                "id": "rule_19",
                "type": "rule",
                "content": {
                  "text": "Use the shared composite actions in `.github/actions` when caching dependencies in GitHub workflows. They provide consistent cache paths and keys:\n\n- `cache-yarn` for Yarn dependencies\n- `cache-bundler` for Ruby gems\n- `cache-gradle` for Gradle wrappers and caches\n- `cache-pods` for CocoaPods",
                  "originalHeader": "CI Caching"
                },
                "metadata": {
                  "strength": "MUST",
                  "format": "Paragraph",
                  "line_start": 107,
                  "line_end": 112
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "rule_20",
                "type": "rule",
                "content": {
                  "text": "Each action accepts an optional `cache-version` input (often combined with `GH_CACHE_VERSION` and a tool-specific version). Avoid calling `actions/cache` directly so future workflows follow the same strategy.",
                  "originalHeader": "CI Caching"
                },
                "metadata": {
